    "### Why We Drop These Columns\n",
    "\n",
    "### Drop `Churn` (the Target)\n",
    "\n",
    "`Churn` is the answer we want the model to predict. If we leave it in the training features, the model just memorizes the answer instead of learning — like copying from an answer sheet.\n",
    "\n",
    "We save it separately as `y` first, then drop it.\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "y        = train_df['Churn'].copy()   # save the answers\n",
    "train_df = train_df.drop('Churn')     # remove from inputs\n",
    "```\n",
    "---\n",
    "### Drop `id` (the Row Number)\n",
    "\n",
    "`id` is just a serial number — it has nothing to do with whether a customer churns. If we leave it in, the model might pick up fake patterns from it and fail on new data.\n",
    "\n",
    "We save it separately only to format the final submission file.\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "train_ids = train_df['id'].copy()   # save for submission\n",
    "train_df  = train_df.drop('id')     # remove from inputs\n",
    "```\n",
    "---\n",
    "**Rule of thumb:** the model should only see columns that genuinely describe the customer not the answer, and not meaningless numbers."
   ]
